This repository starts with a minimal, self-contained governance baseline. The
same checks run locally and in `.github/workflows/devguard.yml`.

Codex starts from `AGENTS.md` and the canonical `.agents/skills/devguard/`
skill; Claude starts from `CLAUDE.md`. Both route to `conventions/README.md` as
the single rules authority. The project-local `.codex/config.toml` contains no
MCP credentials and keeps delegation opt-in.

## PowerShell quick start

Run these commands from the project root:

```powershell
py -3.11 -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pip install -r requirements-dev.txt
git init
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts\install_hooks.py --root .
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts\devguard.py verify --require-hooks
```

The fourth command installs **both** the normal `pre-commit` gate and the
`commit-msg` gate. It also composes existing ECC/global `pre-commit` and
`pre-push` hooks without changing user-level Git configuration, so the same
command is safe for later hook repair. A successful verification prints
`DEVGUARD OK`; every missing dependency, file, configuration link, or required
hook returns a non-zero exit.

## Daily commands

```powershell
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pre_commit run --all-files
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pytest -q
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts\devguard.py verify --require-hooks
```

